    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/top-bingo-stems-satire" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a bingo stem in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A bingo stem is a 6-letter combination that pairs with many different 7th letters to form valid 7-letter words. For example, SATIRE (A, E, I, R, S, T) combines with 20+ different letters to produce bingos like NASTIER, STAINER, and RETAINS. Players memorize the top stems so they can recognize bingo potential the moment it appears on their rack." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best bingo stem in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SATIRE (also arranged as SATINE, TISANE, or RETINAS minus the duplicate) is widely regarded as the single most productive 6-letter bingo stem. It produces over 60 valid 7-letter words depending on which 7th tile is added. RETINA is an equally strong stem sharing 5 of the same letters — together they cover an enormous portion of possible bingos." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many bingo stems should I memorize?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Start with the top 5 (SATIRE, RETINA, SALINE, ORNATE, TISANE) — these alone cover 300+ valid bingos. Within a month, expand to the top 15 stems. Tournament players know 30-50 stems, but the first 15 give you 80% of the practical benefit because the top stems share many letters and overlap heavily." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/bingos/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Bingos</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Top Bingo Stems — SATIRE, RETINA & The Best 6-Letter Foundations</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        A bingo stem is a 6-letter foundation that combines with dozens of different 7th letters to form valid words. Learn the top 15 stems and you'll hold the keys to 800+ bingos — without memorizing each word individually. This guide ranks them by output, shows how they overlap, and gives you a 4-week study plan to internalize them all.
      </p>

      <!-- SECTION 1: What Is a Stem? -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Is a Bingo Stem?</h2>

      <p>A stem is a fixed group of 6 tiles you hold on your rack. When a 7th tile arrives — either drawn from the bag or already sitting on your rack — it combines with the stem to form a valid 7-letter word. The more letters a stem "accepts," the higher your probability of bingo.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Stems vs. Racks</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">A <span class="text-white font-medium">stem</span> is always 6 letters — the foundation waiting for a 7th. A <span class="text-white font-medium">rack</span> is all 7 tiles together. The same physical tiles can be viewed as "stem + extra tile" — this shift in thinking helps you recognize bingo potential faster.</p>
      </div>

      <p>Think of stems as master keys. Instead of memorizing 10,000 individual 7-letter words, you learn 15 keys that unlock 800+ doors. The efficiency is staggering: 15 stems × average 55 bingos each = broad coverage of the entire bingo landscape.</p>

      <!-- Hero card: SATIRE -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 #1 Stem</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">S · A · T · I · R · E</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">66 valid bingos · Accepts 23 different 7th letters · The undisputed king of stems</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">SATIRE and its anagram SATINE are functionally the same stem — the letters A, E, I, R, S, T arranged in any order. Add almost any consonant and several vowels to produce words like NASTIER, RETAINS, STAINER, ANTSIER, DETAINS, and dozens more.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 2: Top 15 Stems Ranked -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Top 15 Bingo Stems Ranked</h2>

      <p>These stems are ranked by total bingo output — the number of distinct valid 7-letter words each can produce. All counts are based on the SOWPODS dictionary (international tournament standard).</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Stem</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letters</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Bingos</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Example Words</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">1</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">SATIRE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I R S T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">66</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">NASTIER, RETAINS, STAINER</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">2</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">RETINA</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I N R T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">63</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">TRAINED, CERTAIN, PAINTER</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">3</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">SALINE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I L N S</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">58</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">ALINERS, NAILERS, SALTINE</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">4</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">ORNATE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E N O R T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">55</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">SENATOR, TREASON, ATONERS</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">5</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">TISANE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I N S T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">54</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">INSTEAD, DETAINS, SAINTED</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">6</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">ARSINE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I N R S</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">52</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">SARDINE, RANDIES, SANDIER</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">7</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">SENORA</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E N O R S</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">50</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">REASONS, PERSONA, ERASION</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">8</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">RETAIL</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I L R T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">48</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">REALIST, SALTIER, RETRIAL</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">9</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">ENTAIL</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I L N T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">46</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">GENITAL, AILMENT, SALIENT</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">SENIOR</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">E I N O R S</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">44</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">EROSION, IRONERS, VERSION</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">11</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">MARINE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E I M N R</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">42</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">REMAINS, SEMINAR, WARMINE</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">12</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">REGAIN</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A E G I N R</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">40</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">READING, WEARING,EARING</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">13</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">LADIES</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A D E I L S</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">38</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">DETAILS, DILATES, DERAILS</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">14</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">ARISTO</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">A I O R S T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">36</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">TRAITOR, ARISTOS, SARTORI</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">15</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-white font-bold font-mono">SORTIE</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">E I O R S T</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-green-400">35</td><td class="px-3 py-3 text-gray-400">STORIED, STEROID, SORTIED</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top stems</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">800+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingos covered</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letters each</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bonus per bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pill badges: top 5 -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SATIRE</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">66 bingos</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RETINA</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">63 bingos</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SALINE</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">58 bingos</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ORNATE</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">55 bingos</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TISANE</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">54 bingos</span></span>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 3: Why Stems Overlap -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why the Top Stems Overlap So Much</h2>

      <p>Look at the top 5 stems closely. SATIRE and RETINA share 5 of 6 letters (A, E, I, R, T — differing only in S vs N). TISANE shares 5 with SATIRE (A, E, I, S, T — swapping R for N). This isn't coincidence — it's the natural consequence of which English letters are most versatile.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🔬 The Core Seven</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The letters <span class="text-white font-medium">A, E, I, N, R, S, T</span> appear in almost every top stem. These seven are the most common in English and appear in the greatest number of word patterns. Any stem built primarily from these letters will be highly productive.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card grid: stem families -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 The SATIRE Family</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SATIRE, TISANE, ARSINE — all share A, I, S, E. Swap one consonant (R↔N↔other) and you get a different stem. Learn one, and you're 80% of the way to learning the others.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 The RETINA Family</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RETINA, ORNATE, RETAIL — all built around A, E, R, T core. The 5th and 6th letters vary (I/N, O/N, I/L), giving each stem access to different word pools while sharing a common backbone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 The O-Stems</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ORNATE, SENORA, SENIOR, ARISTO, SORTIE — these include the letter O, broadening coverage beyond the E/I-heavy stems above. O is less common than E but still highly versatile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔗 The L-Stems</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SALINE, RETAIL, ENTAIL, LADIES — L replaces one of the standard consonants. These cover word families that the R/N-heavy stems miss entirely (SALTINE, AILMENT, DETAILS).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>The practical takeaway: because stems overlap, learning one accelerates learning the next. Your brain builds pattern recognition across related letter groups rather than treating each stem as an isolated memorization task.</p>

      <!-- SECTION 4: Stems vs. Racks -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How Stems Differ from Bingo Racks</h2>

      <p>People often confuse stems with full bingo racks. They're related but distinct concepts that serve different purposes in your study.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📐 Stem (6 letters)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A fixed foundation. You memorize which 7th letters it accepts. Useful <em>before</em> you draw your 7th tile — you know what to hope for. Example: SATIRE → accepts B, C, D, G, K, L, M, N, P, R, W…</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎲 Bingo Rack (7 letters)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">The complete set you hold. You need to anagram it into a word. Useful <em>after</em> you've drawn all tiles — you need to find the valid arrangement. Example: SATIRE+D → TIRADES, DISRATE, ARIDEST.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Why This Distinction Matters</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Stems inform <span class="text-white font-medium">rack leave decisions</span> — which tiles to keep after a play. Racks inform <span class="text-white font-medium">word-finding</span> — what bingo to actually play. The best players think in stems mid-game and switch to rack-thinking when it's time to place tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dig Deeper cross-links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/bingo-racks-to-memorise/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Bingo Racks to Memorise — complete 7-letter combinations ranked by probability</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/bingo-stem-strategy/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Bingo Stem Strategy — the full deep-dive on using stems during live games</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 5: Study Strategy -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">4-Week Stem Learning Plan</h2>

      <p>Don't try to learn all 15 stems at once. Progressive layering — building each week on the last — produces durable memory and faster in-game recognition.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Progressive Study Path</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Week 1 — SATIRE only.</span> Learn every valid 7th letter. Practice anagramming SATIRE+X for 10 minutes daily. Use our word finder to check answers. Goal: instant recognition of SATIRE on your rack.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Week 2 — Add RETINA + SALINE.</span> Notice how RETINA overlaps with SATIRE (5 shared letters). The new words are mostly from the N→S and S→L/N swaps. This week feels easier than week 1 because of overlap.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Week 3 — Add ORNATE + TISANE + ARSINE.</span> You now cover the entire "core seven" letter group in various arrangements. These 6 stems account for 350+ distinct bingos.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Week 4 — Add the remaining 9.</span> SENORA through SORTIE extend your coverage to O-stems, L-stems, and fringe consonant groups. Each new stem adds 35-50 unique words to your repertoire.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Purple strategy tiles -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Test with random draws:</span> Write each stem on a card. Draw a random letter tile from a bag. Within 30 seconds, find a valid bingo. Check with the word finder. Track your hit rate — aim for 80% by end of each week.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Review missed combinations:</span> When a 7th letter stumps you, write down the stem+letter combo. These gaps are where opponents outplay you. Fill them deliberately rather than hoping they stick through repetition.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play stem-aware games:</span> In your next 5 games, consciously ask "do I hold a known stem?" after every draw. Even if you can't find the bingo yet, the habit of recognizing stems on your rack is the foundation everything else builds on.</p>
        </div>
