        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚡ Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Because the top stems share so many letters, <span class="text-white font-medium">learning 15 stems doesn't mean 15× the effort</span>. After SATIRE, each additional stem only introduces 1-2 new letters. Your brain groups them into families, and recognition becomes cumulative rather than linear.</p>
